%blockquote.mainquote
  %p She had a sister called Mary, who seated herself at the Lord’s feet, and listened to his teaching; but Martha was distracted by the many preparations that she was making.
  %p So she went up to Jesus and said: “Lord, do you approve of my sister’s leaving me to make preparations alone? Tell her to help me.”
  %p “Martha, Martha,” replied the Lord, “you are anxious and trouble yourself about many things; but only a few are necessary, or rather One. Mary has chosen the good part, and it will not be taken away from her.”
