    %h4 Nicene Creed
    .copy
      %p
        We believe in one God, the Father Almighty, Maker of heaven and earth, and of all things visible and invisible.
      %p
        And in one Lord Jesus Christ, the only-begotten Son of God, begotten of the Father before all worlds: God from God, Light from Light, true God from true God—begotten, not made—being of one substance with the Father;
      %p
        —By whom all things were made;
      %p
        —Who for us humans, and for our salvation, came down from heaven, and was made flesh, by the Holy Spirit, in the Virgin Mary, and was made human;
      %p
        —He was crucified for us under Pontius Pilate, and suffered, and was buried, and the third day he rose again, according to the Scriptures, and ascended into heaven, and sits on the right hand of the Father;
      %p
        —From thence he shall come again, with glory, to judge the living and the dead;
      %p
        —Whose kingdom shall have no end.
      %p
        And in the Holy Spirit, the Lord and Giver of life, who proceeds from the Father and the Son, who with the Father and the Son together is worshiped and glorified; who spoke by the prophets.
      %p
        In one holy universal and apostolic Church; we acknowledge one baptism for the remission of sins; we look for the resurrection of the dead, and the life of the world to come.
      %p Amen.
